   TOKYO (AP) -- Tokyo stocks dropped sharply Thursday morning as steep declines
on Wall Street dragged down Japanese blue chips and high-technology issues. The
Nikkei Stock Average shed 377.01 points, to 20,456.20 at the end of the morning
