<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 14:34 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Duff: Perelman Kicked Me  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Socialite Patricia Duff says she married
cosmetics billionaire Ronald Perelman before she was ready because
he threatened to ''whack'' her -- and she loved him.
</P>
<P>
   Duff, 46, said that after she separated from movie executive
Mike Medavoy in 1993, Perelman pressured her to marry him, telling
her he would give her the family she desperately wanted.
</P>
<P>
   ''When I hesitated because I needed time to decide,'' Duff said
in court papers, Perelman ''repeatedly threatened that if I went
back to my husband, he would destroy both of us.''
</P>
<P>
   ''He said you are both going to get 'whacked,''' Duff said. ''I
had never heard anyone act or speak like that. His threats seemed
very credible to me as he had the capability and the will to carry
his threats out.''
</P>
<P>
   Duff cited 10 incidents in which she said Perelman hit her,
kicked her and called her names.
</P>
<P>
   She filed the affidavit in her bitter fight with Perelman over
custody of their 5-year-old daughter.
</P>
<P>
   Perelman's lawyer, Adria Hillman, told the judge in the case
that Duff's physical abuse charges are lies.
</P>
<P>
   The custody trial resumes Thursday.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
