<HEADLINE> FedEx worker stabbed to death by co-worker in airport parking lot  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   NEWARK, N.J. (AP) -- A Federal Express employee stabbed a
co-worker to death in a parking lot of Newark International Airport
early Thursday, then confessed to a toll taker on the New Jersey
Turnpike and patiently waited at the toll booth for police to
arrest him, authorities said.
</P>
<P>
   Ernestine Williams of Roselle, 25, was stabbed to death in her
car at about 3:15 a.m. A co-worker, Raheem Wilcox, 21, of
Irvington, was charged with murder.
</P>
<P>
   Steve Coleman, a spokesman for the Port Authority of New York
and New Jersey, which operates the airport, said the two left the
Federal Express building on the airport grounds and went together
to Williams' car in parking lot F.
</P>
<P>
   While they were inside, a struggle ensued, and Williams suffered
a fatal stab wound, he said.
</P>
<P>
   Wilcox fled on foot and ran to the nearby toll booths at New
Jersey Turnpike Interchange 13A just across the city line in
Elizabeth, Coleman said. Once there, he approached a toll collector
and told him what had happened, Coleman said.
</P>
<P>
   The collector called state police, who responded and held him
until Port Authority police arrived. Wilcox waited at the toll
booth for police to arrest him, Coleman said.
</P>
<P>
   Williams was taken to University Hospital in Newark, where she
was pronounced dead at 3:40 a.m.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators said the two had dated at some point, but were not
sure if their relationship had ended before the stabbing.
</P>
<P>
   Wilcox was being held at the Port Authority police facility at
the airport, but was to be taken later in the day to the Essex
County Jail.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
