<HEADLINE> New York Times Earnings Up 35 Pct.  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- The New York Times Co. posted a 35.3 percent
increase in first-quarter earnings, beating Wall Street estimates
as newspaper advertising revenue surged.
</P>
<P>
   The owner of The New York Times, The Boston Globe and 22 other
newspapers earned $83.1 million, or 47 cents a share, in the
January-March period, up from $61.4 million, or 34 cents a share, a
year earlier.
</P>
<P>
   The latest results beat the consensus estimate of 43 cents a
share of analysts surveyed by First Call/Thomson Financial.
</P>
<P>
   Revenue climbed 14.1 percent to $843.2 million from $739.1
million a year earlier.
</P>
<P>
   New York Times shares fell $1.43} to $41.43} in trading at 4:30
p.m. on the New York Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
   ''The year is off to a very strong start with newspaper
advertising revenues up 18.0 percent in the first quarter,'' said
chairman Arthur Sulzberger Jr.
</P>
<P>
   Operating profit increased 38.9 percent in the newspaper group.
Ad revenue rose 19.9 percent at its flagship newspaper and 13.3
percent at the Globe.
</P>
<P>
   At the same time, newsprint expenses fell 3.7 percent due to
lower costs.
</P>
<P>
   Profits were up 5.7 percent in the broadcast group, which
includes eight TV and two radio stations, and were flat in the
magazine group that includes three titles led by Golf Digest.
</P>
<P>
   Separately, the New York Times Co. said it was forming a
purchasing consortium with Knight Ridder to identify the best
suppliers for a range of goods and services including computer
equipment and production supplies.
</P>
<P>
   The consortium will be called KR/NYT Enterprises LLC and ''will
make full use of its considerable marketplace leverage to reduce
costs and create a more efficient purchasing process,'' the
companies said in a statement.
</P>
<P>
   Knight Ridder, based in San Jose, Calif., publishes 31
newspapers.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net: New York Times Co. site: http://www.nytco.com
</P>
<P>
   Knight Ridder site: http://www.kri.com
</P>
</TEXT>
