<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded
heavily Thursday on the New York Stock Exchange, Nasdaq Stock
Market, and American Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
NYSE
</P>
<P>
Advanced Micro Devices, down 4{ at 71{
</P>
<P>
   The chip maker posted a first-quarter profit of $189 million, or
$1.15 per share, nearly twice what most industry analysts expected.
In a conference call following the report, AMD officials predicted
even stronger results for the current quarter.
</P>
<P>
Three-Five Systems Inc., up 5 15/16 at 69 15/16
</P>
<P>
   The company, a maker of liquid crystal display modules, earned
27 cents per share in the first quarter, reversing a loss of 7
cents per share in the first quarter of 1999. Three-Five cited
strong revenue growth due to worldwide demand for mobile handsets.
</P>
