<HEADLINE> Bombs Explode Near Gaza  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   GAZA CITY, Gaza Strip (AP) -- Two small bombs exploded next to an
Israeli military vehicle near an Israeli settlement in the Gaza
Strip Thursday, Palestinian police said. There were no injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Palestinian and Israeli security forces searched the area after
the explosions near the settlement of Netzarim, an isolated Israeli
enclave southwest of Gaza City, said Abdel Razek al-Majaideh,
commander of Palestinian police in Gaza.
</P>
<P>
   The bombs exploded as Israelis were gathering at the settlement
for a ceremony, Israel radio reported. Gunshots were fired at an
Israeli military jeep escorting civilian vehicles, said the radio
report. Israeli forces returned fire.
</P>
<P>
   Palestinians control most of the Gaza Strip, but Israeli
soldiers patrol areas around Jewish settlements. Israeli soldiers
and Palestinian police patrol some of the main roads together. Most
of the settlements are in a bloc at the southern end of the
territory, but Netzarim stands alone near the largest Palestinian
city.
</P>
<P>
   Palestinians demand that all the Israeli settlements be removed
as part of a peace treaty.
</P>
</TEXT>
