<HEADLINE> 1,100 Homes Flooded in Russia  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MOSCOW (AP) -- The Ural River in southern Russia overflowed its
banks and flooded more than 1,100 houses in the town of Orsk, a
news report said Thursday.
</P>
<P>
   Residents are using boats to move around and one person was
reported missing, regional civil defense authorities told the
ITAR-Tass news agency. It said 1,109 houses had been flooded by
Thursday, the report said.
</P>
<P>
   The Ural River runs through the southern Ural Mountains and
flows into the Caspian Sea.
</P>
