<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Explosion Kills Soldier in Hawaii  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SCHOFIELD BARRACKS, Hawaii (AP) -- An explosion during a training
exercise killed one soldier and injured four others, Army officials
said.
</P>
<P>
   The group was learning how to use an explosive device to cut
through concertina wire on an obstacle course at the Pohakuloa
Training Area on the island of Hawaii on Wednesday night, said Maj.
Stan Heath, a public affairs officer.
</P>
<P>
   Investigators have not determined whether the device misfired or
whether another problem caused the accident.
</P>
<P>
   The exercise involved 700 soldiers from the Army's 25th Infantry
Division, which is based at Schofield Barracks on the island of
Oahu.
</P>
<P>
   The names of the victim and the injured soldiers were withheld.
One of those injured has been released and the three who remain
hospitalized were expected to be released Friday, Heath said.
</P>
<P>
   Pohakuloa is located between the Mauna Loa and Mauna Kea
volcanoes and has been used for training since the 1940s.
</P>
</TEXT>
