<DOCNO> APW20000413.0283 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-04-13 23:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rockets 111, Mavericks 102  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- Steve Francis had 16 points, 11 rebounds and
seven assists to lead the Houston Rockets to their fifth straight
win, 111-102 over the Dallas Mavericks on Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   Walt Williams led Houston with 21 points before being ejected
after a fourth-quarter fight with Shawn Bradley.
</P>
<P>
   Cuttino Mobley contributed 20 points and Moochie Norris 19 for
the Rockets, who have won nine of 12 games. Their five-game string
is the longest current winning streak in the NBA.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas saw its own five-game roll end.
</P>
<P>
   Michael Finley led Dallas with 35 points, followed by Dirk
Nowitzki with 15 and Erick Strickland with 14.
</P>
<P>
   Houston moved ahead 85-81 after a 3-pointer by Norris with 9:17
left. The Mavericks then scored seven straight to lead 88-85 with
7:39 remaining. Houston went back in front, leading 98-93 with 4:28
left, before Dallas moved to within 99-97 with 2:59 left.
</P>
<P>
   The Rockets outscored the Mavericks 12-5 after that, with
Francis sinking a 3-pointer with 57 seconds left to give Houston a
107-99 lead that wouldn't be threatened.
</P>
<P>
   Williams and Bradley were ejected with 4:02 left, when Bradley
elbowed Williams in the head after Williams fouled Bradley on a
rebound. Williams then retaliated by punching Bradley in the mouth.
</P>
<P>
   After trailing 57-47 with 10:39 left in the third quarter, the
Mavericks chipped away at the Houston lead to get within 77-75
going into the final period.
</P>
<P>
   Houston forged a 16-10 lead with 4:07 left in the first period
after four straight points by Kenny Thomas. Dallas cut its deficit
to 23-22 going into the second quarter after Finley contributed 13
first-period points.
</P>
<P>
   Dallas led 29-25 early in the second period, before Houston
scored nine straight to lead 34-29 with 6:50 left in the half. The
Mavericks tied the score 38-38 after a 3-pointer by Finley with
3:23 left in the half. The Rockets then outscored the Mavericks
14-4 to lead 52-42 at the half.
</P>
<P>
Notes: Charles Barkley announced Thursday he plans to play in
Houston's final game of the season, at home against the Vancouver
Grizzlies next Wednesday. Barkley retired in December after
rupturing a tendon in his left leg in a game against Philadelphia.
... Mobley leads all reserves with 21 games of 20 or more points.
... Houston is 9-2 with the starting lineup of Francis, Shandon
Anderson, Williams, Thomas and Kelvin Cato. ... With one more
victory, the Mavericks (36-42) will win their most games since
1989-90, when they won 47.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
